<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-364-794  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 364 794.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Computer Systems News  June 19 1989 n422 p16(2).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Sun sued by shareholder. (Sun Microsystems Inc.)andM;</TITLE><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Sun Microsystems Inc is being sued by a shareholder who allegesthat the company acted to inflate the market price of thecompany's stock 'by misstating and concealing material informationconcerning SM's financial and operating condition and outlook.'andO;New products, strong financial results and a possible agreementwith with Toshiba Corp all made Sun's stock rise to inflatedlevels, according to the complaint.andP;  Then Sun shocked shareholdersby announcing depressed revenue and the possibility of a loss forthe fourth quarter.andP;  Plaintiff Elaine Lowell of San Jose filed aclass action suit on behalf of all shareholders who may have beenmisled by Sun's actions.andP;  The Federal District Court will decideon whether the complaint defines an acceptable class for thisaction.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   Sun Microsystems Inc. (cases).andO;Ticker:    SUNW.andO;Topic:     Law SuitRevenueProfitFinancial ReportFinancial Stability.andO;Feature:   illustrationportrait.andO;Caption:   Scott McNealy. (portrait)andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>